image.altText: A Giants AFL player jumps in the air in celebration as a smiling teammate points at him after a goal.

items.synopsis: The Giants are into a cut-throat semifinal after an impressive elimination final performance that puts paid to St Kilda's season. Follow the action in our live blog.

title.children: Giants make a big, big sound at the MCG to end St Kilda's season

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: It was Giants footy at its very best today — fast, furious and deadly efficient. The Saints defence, among the best in the league in 2023, had no answers to the might of GWS today. It's a disappointing finish to the year for a St Kilda team that took big steps forward under Ross Lyon this year, but they were taken out of their comfort zone today and soundly beaten by a better team. Work to do in the offseason for the Saints, but the Giants don't look done yet in 2023. Whether it's Brisbane or Port Adelaide, they should be wary of the Orange Tsunami.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: FULL-TIME: Giants win by 24 points! Season over for St Kilda!

children.content: It was Giants footy at its very best today — fast, furious and deadly efficient. The Saints defence, among the best in the league in 2023, had no answers to the might of GWS today.

It's a disappointing finish to the year for a St Kilda team that took big steps forward under Ross Lyon this year, but they were taken out of their comfort zone today and soundly beaten by a better team.
Work to do in the offseason for the Saints, but the Giants don't look done yet in 2023. Whether it's Brisbane or Port Adelaide, they should be wary of the Orange Tsunami.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: It was all over bar the shouting five minutes ago. But goals to Owens, Hill and Wanganeen-Milera just before the buzzer have given St Kilda hope again, and will have GWS just a little bit twitchy. Somehow the Saints have wrestled back momentum. It would take one of the greatest comebacks we've ever seen in a final, but right now it feels possible. One quarter to play. No point leaving anything in the tank. It all comes down to this.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Three-quarter-time: Giants lead is back to 25 points

children.content: It was all over bar the shouting five minutes ago. But goals to Owens, Hill and Wanganeen-Milera just before the buzzer have given St Kilda hope again, and will have GWS just a little bit twitchy.
Somehow the Saints have wrestled back momentum. It would take one of the greatest comebacks we've ever seen in a final, but right now it feels possible.
One quarter to play. No point leaving anything in the tank. It all comes down to this.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: There is life in these Saints! It was a 42-point game not too long ago, but St Kilda have found four of the last five goals to drag themselves back into it. The Giants were mighty impressive throughout most of that quarter, but the door has been left ajar. St Kilda clearly aren't going to win this on the strength of their defence — GWS are cutting through them with ease. But when the Saints start winning some of their own ball and start moving it with confidence, it's a different game. They're coming from a long way back, but you can't count out the Saints.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Half-time: Giants lead it by 23 points

children.content: There is life in these Saints!
It was a 42-point game not too long ago, but St Kilda have found four of the last five goals to drag themselves back into it.

The Giants were mighty impressive throughout most of that quarter, but the door has been left ajar. St Kilda clearly aren't going to win this on the strength of their defence — GWS are cutting through them with ease.
But when the Saints start winning some of their own ball and start moving it with confidence, it's a different game.
They're coming from a long way back, but you can't count out the Saints.
